---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FraiseQL for DevOps Engineers - Deployment & Operations"
  description="Production deployment, monitoring, and operations guide for FraiseQL servers."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>🚀 FraiseQL for DevOps Engineers</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #666;">
      <strong>Production-ready deployment and operations for GraphQL APIs</strong>
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Your Role</h2>
      <p>
        As a DevOps engineer, you're responsible for:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Deploying FraiseQL servers to production</li>
        <li>Managing database migrations and schema versions</li>
        <li>Monitoring performance and availability</li>
        <li>Implementing zero-downtime deployments</li>
        <li>Handling secrets, TLS, and security</li>
        <li>Scaling infrastructure under load</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Deployment: Works Everywhere</h2>
      <p style="color: #666; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        FraiseQL runs on any infrastructure: bare metal, containers, VMs, Kubernetes, cloud providers (AWS, GCP, Azure), or self-hosted. Choose what works for your organization.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Binary Deployment</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Download fraiseql-cli
wget https://releases.fraiseql.dev/fraiseql-cli-linux-amd64

# Compile schema and SQL templates
./fraiseql-cli compile schema.json fraiseql.toml
# Outputs: schema.compiled.json (immutable, deploy-ready)

# Deploy server binary
./fraiseql-server --config fraiseql.toml --schema schema.compiled.json

# Server is ready to receive GraphQL queries`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Container Deployment</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Dockerfile (works with Docker, Podman, containerd, etc.)
FROM ghcr.io/fraiseql/fraiseql-server:latest

COPY schema.compiled.json /app/
COPY fraiseql.toml /app/

EXPOSE 4000
CMD ["fraiseql-server", "--config", "fraiseql.toml", "--schema", "schema.compiled.json"]

# Build and run
docker build -t my-api:1.0 .
docker run -p 4000:4000 -e DATABASE_URL=postgres://... my-api:1.0
podman build -t my-api:1.0 .    # Podman also works`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Kubernetes / Orchestration</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Helm chart available at https://charts.fraiseql.dev/

helm install fraiseql fraiseql/fraiseql \\
  --set image.tag=latest \\
  --set replicas=3 \\
  --set resources.requests.cpu=500m \\
  --set resources.requests.memory=512Mi \\
  -f values.yaml

# Or use fraisier orchestrator for zero-downtime deploys
fraisier deploy \\
  --schema schema.compiled.json \\
  --blue-env production-blue \\
  --green-env production-green \\
  --health-query "query { __typename }"
`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Self-Hosted (Proxmox, VMware, Hyperv, etc.)</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Deploy as binary on any hypervisor
# 1. Create VM with Linux (Ubuntu, CentOS, Alpine, etc.)
# 2. Copy fraiseql-server binary
# 3. Copy schema.compiled.json and fraiseql.toml
# 4. Configure network and database connectivity
# 5. systemd unit file for auto-start

[Unit]
Description=FraiseQL GraphQL Server
After=network.target postgresql.service

[Service]
Type=simple
User=fraiseql
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/fraiseql-server \\
  --config /etc/fraiseql/fraiseql.toml \\
  --schema /etc/fraiseql/schema.compiled.json
Restart=on-failure

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Cloud Deployment (AWS, GCP, Azure, etc.)</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Option 1: Deploy as container
# AWS ECS, Google Cloud Run, Azure Container Instances, etc.
# Use same container image as above

# Option 2: Lambda / Serverless Function
# Package fraiseql-server with schema for FaaS platforms
# (cold start: ~50-200ms depending on platform)

# Option 3: Cloud VMs (EC2, Compute Engine, Azure VM)
# Same as binary deployment + systemd unit file above

# Example: AWS Lambda with custom runtime
# 1. Package fraiseql-server as Lambda custom runtime
# 2. Deploy schema.compiled.json as Lambda function package
# 3. API Gateway + Lambda integration for GraphQL endpoint`}</code></pre>

      <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem; padding: 1rem; background: #f0fdf4; border-left: 4px solid #059669; border-radius: 4px;">
        <strong>The compiled artifact</strong> (<code>schema.compiled.json</code>) <strong>is platform-agnostic.</strong> Deploy it anywhere you run the fraiseql-server binary.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Configuration Management</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">fraiseql.toml (Compile-Time Configuration)</h3>
      <pre><code>{`[fraiseql]
name = "my-api"
version = "1.0.0"

[fraiseql.server]
host = "0.0.0.0"
port = 4000
max_connections = 100

[fraiseql.security.rate_limiting]
enabled = true
auth_start_max_requests = 100
auth_start_window_secs = 60

[fraiseql.security.audit_logging]
enabled = true
log_level = "info"

[fraiseql.security.field_encryption]
enabled = true
key_rotation_days = 90`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Environment Variables (Runtime Overrides)</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Database connection
DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@host:5432/db

# Server settings
FRAISEQL_HOST=0.0.0.0
FRAISEQL_PORT=4000
FRAISEQL_LOG_LEVEL=info

# TLS certificates
FRAISEQL_TLS_CERT=/etc/certs/cert.pem
FRAISEQL_TLS_KEY=/etc/certs/key.pem

# Secrets management
FRAISEQL_VAULT_ADDR=https://vault.example.com
FRAISEQL_VAULT_TOKEN=\${VAULT_TOKEN}

# Rate limiting override
FRAISEQL_RATE_LIMIT_BURST=200
FRAISEQL_RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW=60`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Database Migrations</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Using confiture</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# confiture handles schema versioning automatically
# 600× faster than traditional migrations

# Automatic migration on deploy
confiture migrate --database postgres --schema schema.compiled.json

# Supports multiple strategies:
# 1. DDL Build (dev/test, <1s): Full schema rebuild
# 2. Incremental (local dev): Fast delta updates
# 3. Production Sync (zero-downtime): Blue/green migration
# 4. Multi-agent (parallel): Distributed schema coordination`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Monitoring & Observability</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Prometheus Metrics</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Metrics exposed on :9090/metrics

fraiseql_graphql_queries_total{query_type="read"}
fraiseql_graphql_mutations_total{mutation_type="create"}
fraiseql_query_duration_ms{query_name="GetUserWithPosts", percentile="p99"}
fraiseql_db_connection_pool{state="active"}
fraiseql_db_connection_pool{state="idle"}
fraiseql_rate_limit_events_total{endpoint="/graphql"}
fraiseql_audit_log_entries_total{mutation="create_post"}

# Grafana dashboard available at:
# https://grafana.com/grafana/dashboards/fraiseql`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Distributed Tracing (OpenTelemetry)</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# FraiseQL exports traces for all queries
# Configuration:

[fraiseql.observability]
tracing_enabled = true
otel_exporter_otlp_endpoint = "http://jaeger:4317"

# Each GraphQL query gets:
# - Trace ID (correlates across services)
# - Span: Query parsing
# - Span: Query compilation
# - Span: SQL generation
# - Span: Database execution
# - Span: Result serialization`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Structured Logging</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# All logs are JSON for easy aggregation
# Ship to ELK, Datadog, CloudWatch, etc.

{
  "timestamp": "2024-02-06T12:34:56Z",
  "level": "INFO",
  "service": "fraiseql",
  "event": "query_executed",
  "query_name": "GetUserWithPosts",
  "duration_ms": 2.5,
  "db_queries": 1,
  "user_id": "user-123",
  "trace_id": "abc123def456"
}

# Severity levels: DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR, FATAL`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Scaling & Performance</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Connection Pooling</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Configure in fraiseql.toml
[fraiseql.database]
pool_size = 20
pool_timeout_secs = 30
idle_timeout_secs = 300

# For 100,000 req/sec:
# - Need ~1000 connections total (10 servers × 100 connections each)
# - Database connection limit: 2000+
# - Each request uses connection for <1ms (fast queries)`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Horizontal Scaling</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# All FraiseQL instances are stateless
# Load balance across N servers

# Each server handles requests independently
# No session affinity needed (schema is pre-compiled)
# Scale up/down based on CPU and request volume

# Recommended autoscaling:
# - CPU threshold: 70% → scale up
# - CPU threshold: 30% → scale down
# - Min replicas: 3 (high availability)
# - Max replicas: 100 (burst capacity)`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Production Runbooks</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Scenario: Performance Degradation</h3>
      <pre><code>{`1. Check metrics: Prometheus dashboard
   - Query latency spiking?
   - Connection pool exhausted?
   - Database CPU high?

2. Identify slow queries
   - Pull query traces from Jaeger
   - Look for N+1 patterns (shouldn't exist in FraiseQL)
   - Check for database lock contention

3. Solutions
   - Scale up servers (if CPU-bound)
   - Add database read replicas (if DB CPU-bound)
   - Check for index missing (run pg_tviews refresh)

4. Root cause
   - Schema change broke assumptions?
   - Recompile with fraiseql-cli
   - Deploy new schema.compiled.json with fraisier`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Scenario: Database Migration Failure</h3>
      <pre><code>{`1. Detected: confiture migration rollback
   - Transaction failed (schema conflict)
   - Constraint violation

2. Immediate action
   - Database still on previous version (safe)
   - No data loss

3. Resolution
   - Review migration logs: confiture migration-logs
   - Fix constraint in schema definition
   - Recompile: fraiseql compile schema.json
   - Retry migration: confiture migrate --retry`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Scenario: Zero-Downtime Deploy</h3>
      <pre><code>{`1. Using fraisier orchestrator
   $ fraisier deploy --schema schema.compiled.json \\
       --blue-env prod-blue --green-env prod-green

2. Process
   - Compile new schema
   - Deploy to GREEN environment
   - Run health checks against GREEN
   - If all pass: Switch traffic BLUE → GREEN (instant)
   - If any fail: Rollback (keep BLUE active)

3. Result
   - Zero downtime
   - Instant rollback if needed
   - Old environment still running (fallback)`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Security & Secrets</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">HashiCorp Vault Integration</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Store secrets in Vault, not in code

[fraiseql.secrets]
vault_addr = "https://vault.example.com"
vault_path = "secret/fraiseql/prod"
auto_rotate_days = 30

# Credentials automatically rotated
# FraiseQL handles refresh without restart`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">TLS/HTTPS</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# Enable TLS
[fraiseql.server]
tls_enabled = true
tls_cert_path = "/etc/certs/cert.pem"
tls_key_path = "/etc/certs/key.pem"

# Or use environment variables
FRAISEQL_TLS_CERT=/etc/certs/cert.pem
FRAISEQL_TLS_KEY=/etc/certs/key.pem

# Certificate rotation: Use cert-manager (Kubernetes) or similar`}</code></pre>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Audit Logging</h3>
      <pre><code>{`# All mutations are logged for compliance
# 100% audit trail (not sampled)

[fraiseql.security.audit_logging]
enabled = true
destination = "postgres"  # or "elasticsearch"
retention_days = 2555     # 7 years

# Each audit log contains:
# - Timestamp
# - User ID
# - Mutation type
# - Input parameters (sanitized)
# - Result
# - Signature (HMAC-SHA256)`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Disaster Recovery</h2>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Backup Strategy</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Database backups:</strong> WAL-based continuous backup (PostgreSQL)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Configuration backups:</strong> Git repo for fraiseql.toml and schema changes
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Compiled schema backups:</strong> Archive schema.compiled.json versions
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Recovery Procedures</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Service failure:</strong> Restart fraiseql-server (stateless, &lt;5s recovery)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Database failure:</strong> Point-in-time recovery from WAL backups
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Schema corruption:</strong> Rollback to previous schema.compiled.json version
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Quick Reference: Commands</h2>
      <pre><code>{`# Compile schema
fraiseql-cli compile schema.json fraiseql.toml

# Run server
fraiseql-server --config fraiseql.toml --schema schema.compiled.json

# Database migration
confiture migrate --database postgres --schema schema.compiled.json

# Deploy with fraisier
fraisier deploy --schema schema.compiled.json \\
  --blue-env production-blue \\
  --green-env production-green

# Check health
curl http://localhost:4000/health
# Returns: { "status": "ok", "uptime": "..." }

# View metrics
curl http://localhost:9090/metrics | grep fraiseql

# Read logs
docker logs fraiseql-server | jq .`}</code></pre>
    </section>

